# Python to Rust Atlas

Use this rule for Python-to-Rust migration questions, reference lookups, and
side-by-side code rewrites.

- Read `AGENTS.md` for the main workflow.
- Use `.github/skills/python-rust-atlas/references/concepts.md` for conceptual
  mapping.
- Use `.github/skills/python-rust-atlas/references/patterns.md` for code
  rewrites.
- Use `.github/skills/python-rust-atlas/references/official-links.md` or
  `official-references.md` when citations are needed.
- Explain the Rust mental model first, then show code.
- Prefer idiomatic Rust over Python-like transliterations.
- Call out ownership, borrowing, `Option`/`Result`, and async runtime tradeoffs
  when they matter.
